A2098 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TAHOE-QUAKES-SFCHRON(     04-01 0106
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TAHOE-QUAKES-SFCHRON(CORRECTION) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
(EDS: CORRECTS FIGURE IN 14TH GRAF OF NEW QUAKE FEARS IN
TAHOE  REGION)
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   In a report published in the journal Science earlier this month,
Thatcher and his colleagues found that for 125 miles or so, the
crust in the western part of the Basin and Range abutting the
Sierra is being steadily squeezed at a rate of 21/2 inches a year
northwestward against the more stable crustal block of the Sierra.
That's an inexorable crunch easily powerful enough to fracture the
deep crusts into seismic faults.
</P>
<P>
   (PICK UP 15TH GRAF: In Reno, Schweickert, Lahren and Smith
recently briefed ...)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
