<HEADLINE>
HOW TO COMMUNICATE WITH BELL'S DESCENDANTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to any living relatives of Alexander Graham
Bell?
</P>
<P>
   _ V.T., Kingston, Pa.
</P>
<P>
   A: Bell has two surviving grandchildren: Mabel H. Grosvenor, 94,
and Elsie ``Carol'' Myers, 88.
</P>
<P>
   You can contact them in care of another descendant, Edwin
Grosvenor, at 4600 N. Park Ave., Suite 200, Chevy Chase, MD 20815.
</P>
<P>
   Edwin Grosvenor is the author of ``Alexander Graham Bell,'' a
1997 biography. Another descendant, great-grandson Gil Grosvenor,
is the chairman of the National Geographic Society.
</P>
<P>
   Bell was president of the society from 1898 until 1899, when he
hired future son-in-law Gilbert Hovey Grosvenor to replace him. The
society was founded by Bell's father-in-law, Gardiner Greene
Hubbard, and 32 other members in 1888.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I heard that Greta Van Susteren is married to somebody who
works in the White House. Is this true?
</P>
<P>
   _ I.T., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Van Susteren is married to John Coale, who is also her
partner in a Washington law firm.
</P>
<P>
   Coale, who participated in lawsuits against tobacco companies,
was one of the first to file suit last year against gun makers
alleging that they contribute to urban crime.
</P>
<P>
   Coale does not work in the White House but did contribute
$25,000 to national Democratic groups in 1998, including $10,000 to
the Democratic National Committee, according to news reports.
</P>
<P>
   In a recent profile of Coale in The Economist, he described
himself as a ``frequent visitor'' to the White House. The magazine
reports that his office has pictures of him with President Clinton,
Hillary Clinton and ``in the ultimate triumph of insiderism, with
Socks, the Clintons' cat.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where does Anne Geddes find all those adorable babies, and
where can I write to her?
</P>
<P>
   _ C.M., Shrewsbury, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Geddes in care of Geddes Group Licensing, 9200
Sunset Blvd., Suite 706, Los Angeles, CA 90069.
</P>
<P>
   Geddes, who primarily photographs newborns and 6-month-olds,
lives and works in New Zealand. The parents of many subjects find
her, but she does sometimes advertise, depending on the project she
is undertaking, a representative of the Geddes Group said.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Geddes came to the United States and advertised for
photographic subjects, but she has no current plans to return.
</P>
<P>
   She has an official World Wide Web site at www.annegeddes.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
