</P>
<P>
   RECKLESS-SKIING (Breckenridge, Colo.) _ Ski resorts are taking a
new hard line on reckless skiing after a hard winter in Colorado in
which resorts already have recorded 12 skiers killed in collisions,
double the season average and the highest number in over a decade.
Breckenridge has been the hardest hit, recording five of the
fatalities during a one month period in mid-winter. By James
Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   NM-TORTURE (Elephant Butte, N.M.) _ A woman accused in a bizarre
kidnap-sexual torture case told an acquaintance she joined her
boyfriend in the tortures for the adrenaline rush. She is also
reported to have said that four to six people had been killed,
mutilated and dumped in Elephant Butte Lake, 150 miles south of
Albuquerque _ and that more bodies were buried in the desert. There
has been no indication from police that bodies have been found, but
authorities have not ruled out the possibility of homicides. By Don
Terry.
</P>
