deal, with the former company agreeing to pay $26.8 billion in
stock to buy the latter. The price is 26 percent above ARCO's value
last Friday, before the two companies confirmed they were holding
talks. The transaction is the fourth major acquisition in the oil
industry since August. By Agis Salpukas.
