Vice President Al Gore, who is stuck with the administration's
policy, and the making of potential GOP presidential candidate John
McCain, who is free to be a tough-minded hawk without being held
responsible for mistakes along the way. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEDICAID-CUTOFF (Washington) _ Despite a painful, crippling
disease, Eva Amey of Elmira, N.Y. got herself off welfare more than
a year ago and is working as a teacher's aide. But she earns only
$5,756 a year and, because she is now employed, has lost her
Medicaid benefits. With medical bills averaging more than $500 a
month, she often finds she can't afford to see the doctor or buy
medicine. Health care advocates say there are tens of thousands
cases like Amey's. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
