(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in the ``e''
entertainment news file. For questions, contact Bob McCarthy at
(818) 713-3665. 
 
 
LIV-TYLER (Los Angeles) _ Liv Tyler seems to have come through a
lifetime of celebrity more or less unaffected. By Bob Strauss. 
 
 
COOKIES-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ ``Cookie's Fortune'' feels like time
well-spent. By Bob Strauss. 3 stars 
 
 
TOWNERS-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ ``The Out-of-Towners'' fills a need
for a light, adult comedy. It's just too bad that it's not better.
By Marla Matzer. 2 1/2 stars 
 
 
DREAMLIFE-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ A free spirit and a pessimist
become friends in this intimate character study, ``The Dreamlife of
Angels.'' By Glenn Whipp. 3 stars 
 
 
VIDEO-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Peter Sellers did some of his best
on-screen work with Blake Edwards in the ``Pink Panther'' movies,
four of which are now on DVD. By Rob Lowman 
 
 
SWAMP-ROCKER (Los Angeles) _ Tony Joe White's 11th album is still
on hold and may not be issued by the label in the U.S. at all. By
Fred Shuster. 
 
 
DISC-REVIEWS (Los Angeles) _ Record reviews. Daily News Staff. 
 
 
SHARPS-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Journalist Sharony Andrews Green, who
was a relative of Grant Green's, has written a biography about this
underrated session guitarist. By Fred Shuster. 
 
 

