<P>
   SCI-STEM-CELLS (Undated) _ In more progress in the search to use
people's own tissues to cure their ills, researchers report that
they have cultured the stem cells from which bone, cartilege,
tendons and stroma (a little known but crucial bone component)
grow. By Nicholas Wade. (1000 words)
