<P>
   ENNIO-COMEDY (New York) _ Imagine, if you will, an evening with
Roberto Benigni, doing impressions of Stevie Wonder, Edith Piaf,
Fidel Castro, Marilyn Monroe, Barbra Streisand and the Pope. Now
imagine him impersonating them all in a lip-synching dumb show,
with paper headdresses, costumes and props affixed to his scalp and
torso. No, this wouldn't necessarily be your scariest post-Academy
Awards show hallucination. It would, in fact, be an approximation
of ``Ennio,'' an honest-to-goodness Off Broadway show starring
Ennio Marchetto that, ahem, unfolds like no other production in
town. By Peter Marks.
