the center of the engrossing, challenging exhibition of early
drawings by the German painter Sigmar Polke. The third gallery in
this show, which has been organized by Margit Rowell, curator of
drawings, and is devoted to works from 1963 to 1974, presents only
four drawings, all dated 1971-72. By Roberta Smith.
