major sports figure in another investigation. The final day of the
Trois Jours de La Panne race was canceled in Bruseels after the
police discovered drugs believed to be intended for the sport's top
racing team. Police said the race could continue without the
Mapei-Quick Step riders, but other team managers refused, and the
race was abandoned. By Samuel Abt.
