<P>
   &QR;  June 19-July 28: Benson &AMP; Hedges International Fireworks
Competition, Montreal. Masters in the art of pyrotechnics from
around the world compete. 514-872-4537.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  July 1-11: Montreal International Jazz Festival, Montreal.
More than 2,000 musicians from 20 countries will perform an array
of jazz selections. The heart of downtown will be the site for 100
indoor ticketed concerts and 300 free outdoor performances.
514-523-3378.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  July 8-18: du Maurier Quebec City Summer Festival, Quebec
City. More than 800 performers from 20 countries will participate
in North America's greatest urban experience dedicated to street
and stage performing arts. Information: 1-888-515-0515; tickets:
1-800-361-4595.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  July 14-25: Just for Laughs Festival, Montreal. More than 600
comedians from 14 countries appear in 1,000 shows at outdoor and
indoor venues throughout the city. 514-845-3155.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Sept. 3-6: Gatineau Hot Air Balloon Festival, Gatineau. More
than 150 balloons will be involved, including those in shapes of a
Mountie, maple leaf, snowman, sun, pumpkin, cow and a 150-foot
Statue of Liberty. 819-243-2330.
</P>
<P>
   NOVA SCOTIA
</P>
<P>
   explore.gov.ns.ca
</P>
<P>
   1-800-565-0000
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  July 1-Sept. 26: Shakespeare by the Sea, Halifax. The Bard's
works are performed outdoors in the batteries and forts of Point
Pleasant Park at the mouth of Halifax Harbor. 902-422-0295.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  June 30-July 7: Nova Scotia International Tattoo, Halifax.
More than 2,000 military and civilians participants from around the
world gather for this massive indoor event. 902-420-1114.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  July 16-18: Antigonish Highland Games. Oldest continuous
traditional Scottish Highland games in North America. Competition,
outdoor tattoo and more. 902-863-4275.
</P>
<P>
   NEW BRUNSWICK
</P>
