started in 1983. (Note, this is far from the largest increase as
far as percentages, just the largest in raw numbers. In several
years there has been a larger actual growth, based on percentage of
growth). (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-PRICELINE _ Delta Air Lines may have hit the gold mine
with Priceline.com, the latest redhot Internet stock. When Delta
agreed last year to be listed on the travel site and got options to
buy 11 million shares at $1.16 a share. The stock went public this
week at $12 and zoomed to $82. Not clear how or when Delta can
exercise the options, but right now it has a paper profit of about
$880 million. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
