<P>
   MISSING SOLDIERS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HUNTSVILLE, Texas _ The East Texas town of Huntsville is best
known for its prison and a succession of executions. But today the
town is festooned with yellow ribbons because one of the U.S. Army
soldiers captured on the border of Macedonia and Kosovo, Spec.
Steven M. Gonzales, calls Huntsville home. Gonzalez's family lives
in Huntsville, where his father is a prison employee, and he
graduated from high school in another East Texas town, Palestine.
News conference with family scheduled for 3:15 p.m. CST. By JOHN
MORITZ and MICHELLE MELENDEZ. Story will move in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
