<P>
   JOHNSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ It is evident that the Serbs are executing a genocidal
plan in Kosovo reminiscent of the Khmer Rouge infamy in Cambodia.
Still, there are those who question the need for and the
humanitarian motivation of the U.S.-led North Atlantic Treaty
Organization airstrikes against the rampaging Serbian military
machine. They pose the rhetorical question: Why Kosovo and not a
number of other places in the world where people are being
slaughtered, cast out of their homes and sent on the refugee roads?
By CECIL JOHNSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F I N A N C I A L &QL; 
