<P>
   GAS-EXPENSIVE (Los Angeles) _ With gas prices continuing to
rise, seemingly every hour, frustrated Southern California drivers
held a protest at a downtown L.A. gas station while a local TV
station has broadcast a hotline for finding the best price. Long
lines are bringing back memories of the 1970s oil crisis, only this
time everybody's got a fuel-guzzling sport-utility vehicle. By
Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-OFFICE-MIDWEEK (Los Angeles) _ Sci-fi thriller ``The
Matrix'' opened at 2,849 theaters with an eye at breaking the box
office record for a spring break Wednesday opening. By Dave McNary.
