</P>
<P>
   MURDOCH-MALONE (New York) _ Folo on reports that Rupert Murdoch
has agreed to take control of a group of regional cable-television
networks and an expanded stake in two New York sports franchises,
the Knicks and Rangers, by buying out his sports partner, the cable
maverick John Malone. By Geraldine Fabrikant.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-STEM-CELLS (Undated) _ Researchers have isolated a master
cell from adult bone marrow that can be directed to grow bone,
cartilage, tendons or another vital bone component, a feat that
experts call a major step toward learning to make replacement parts
for ailing or aged bodies. By Nicholas Wade
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   NIRELAND-TALKS (Belfast, Northern Ireland) _ Talks adjourned
inconclusively in Northern Ireland, but Prime Minister Tony Blair
of Britain said he thought they had established a ``satisfactory
basis'' for a final settlement. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:15 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
