<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, APRIL 2
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-ISRAEL-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Mar. 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Mar.
31, about candidates' efforts to win the votes of Israeli Arabs in
the Israeli election on May 17 misidentified a town visited this
week by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. It was Shefaram, not
Shfayim.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INEXPENSIVE-COMPUTERS-NYT (moved on Sunday, Mar. 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Mar. 28,
about a personal computer being offered by the Microworkz
Corporation for $299 misstated one of the details of the offer. It
does indeed include Microsoft Windows 98 software.
</P>
</TEXT>
