minorities, opening the doors to Yale, from which he graduated
magna cum laude.
 &HT;    As the first individual who is neither black nor white to be
selected for this position, Lee signals that everyone has a stake
in the civil rights movement. As an Asian American representing the
Legal Defense Fund, he gave meaning to the metaphor of ``building
bridges.''
 &HT;    Both before joining the Justice Department and now as one of its
officials, his clients have included people of all identities. The
hallmark of his approach has been resolving difficult disputes
through settlements helping all parties. He demonstrates how
diversity can work.
 &HT;    If the Senate says yes to Lee, it will not only benefit the
people whose civil rights he would protect, but also restore public
