since late 1997, but President Clinton recently re-submitted his
name to a hostile Senate in another effort at confirmation, notes
columnist Frank Wu. ``Lee is better than qualified,'' he writes. He
spent 20 years at the Legal Defense Fund where, as an Asian
American, he gave meaning to the words `building bridges.' ``Both
before joining the Justice Department and now as one of its
officials, his clients have included people of all identities,'' Wu
declares. ``He demonstrates how diversity can work,''
</P>
<P>
   Moved as BC-LANN-LEE:WU-NEWAMERICA-NYTSF in ``k'' commentary and
``a'' general news files.
</P>
