soldiers were captured by Serbs on Thursday. The Americans had been
part of the U.N. peacekeeping force which has been in Macedonia
since 1993. (Alan Chin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) AOMORI, Japan -- April 1, 1999 -- JAPAN-ORIGINS, 4-01 --
The archeologist Yasuhiro Okada at Aomori, with a reconstructed
tower and houses of the early Jomon people in the background. The
origins of the Japanese people remain a much-debated puzzle, but
part of it is being pieced together here on the vast archeological
site some 375 miles north of Tokyo. (Nicholas D. Kristoff/New York
Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
