and marching its ethnic Albanians out through gantlets of masked,
heavily armed Serbs. (Edward Keating/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) NEW YORK -- April 1, 1999 -- WEIR-THEATER-REVIEW, 4-01 --
The cast of Conor McPherson's play ``The Weir,'' which opened
Thursday night at the Walter Kerr, includes, from left, Kieran
Ahern, Dermot Crowley, Brendan Coyle, Jim Norton and Michelle
Fairley. Under the seamless, gentle direction of Ian Rickson, the
show's five actors make an unforgettable case for the impossibility
of distinguishing the teller from the tale. (Sara Krulwich/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
