<SLUG> BC-BBO-FREEWAY-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CALL IT THE DETOUR SERIES?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM _ The Freeway Series has been reduced to the Freeway
Game. By next year, the annual Dodgers-Angels preseason get
together in SoCal could be extinct.
</P>
<P>
   Several factors could put an end to the long-standing tradition,
including the Dodgers' desire to play exhibition games outside the
country.
</P>
<P>
   Dodgers president and CEO Bob Graziano said the club is looking
into playing an exhibition game _ or games _ next year in either
the Dominican Republic, Mexico or Asia.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've explored that in the past and we'll do it again,''
Graziano said. ``It all depends on the logistics of the situation,
and what other teams are doing. It could be done (next year) if
there was something that made sense.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers and Angels have played in the Freeway Series each
year since 1981, and have played all but three times since 1962.
Tonight (7:05 p.m.) the teams play at Anaheim's Edison Field.
</P>
<P>
   If the Dodgers elect to play exhibition games against another
country's all-star team, it would follow the path blazed by the New
York Mets and Baltimore Orioles this spring. The Mets traveled to
the Dominican Republic to play an exhibition game last month while
the Orioles played in Cuba last Sunday, marking the first time a
U.S. team had played in Cuba in 40 years.
</P>
<P>
   Given the Dodgers' history with the Dominican Republic, Mexico
and Asia, it would make sense for them to play there. The Dodgers
are considered pioneers in developing players in those regions.
</P>
<P>
   Campo Los Palmas, the Dodgers' baseball academy in the Dominican
Republic, is entering its 13th season. The Dodgers have tapped into
the Asian baseball market with the signings of Hideo Nomo and Chan
Ho Park. And Fernando Valenzuela's success during the '80s linked
the Dodgers to Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've had surface talk,'' Dodgers general manager Kevin Malone
said. ``We'd be interested in exploring those opportunities, but we
haven't really looked into it in any detail. It could be worked
out. I think we'd be interested in doing that again. We haven't
talked about any details, but we would be interested in exploring
those opportunities.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers played the Milwaukee Brewers in an exhibition game
in Monterrey, Mexico, in 1991 and took postseason trips to Japan
and Taiwan to play in a Friendship Series in 1993. The club made
frequent trips to the Dominican Republic and Cuba in the 1940s.
</P>
<P>
   Graziano said the structure of upcoming regular-season schedules
will dictate, largely, what the Dodgers do. It wouldn't make sense
to travel to Asia for exhibition games unless the Dodgers open the
season on the West Coast.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the Dodgers' possible spring training move is another
factor in continuing some form of the Freeway Series. If the
Dodgers move from Vero Beach, Fla., to the Fort McDowell Indian
Reservation near Phoenix, the two teams would play several times in
the Cactus League.
</P>
<P>
   Already, much of the luster has been taken off the preseason
series because of interleague play. The teams play six times during
the regular season. Graziano said that's part of the reason the
Dodgers opted out of two of the three Freeway Series games this
season.
</P>
<P>
   ``From my perspective, it's something we're going to have to
revise,'' Graziano said. ``I didn't want to put an end to the
Freeway Series, but at some point you're going to have to look at
it and see if it's better to play exhibition games (with other
teams).
</P>
<P>
   ``It depends on what the alternatives are, and we found out this
year there can be some pretty attractive alternatives. But we want
to make sure there are alternatives on both sides.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers will host the defending World Series champion New
York Yankees on Saturday and Sunday. The Angels play the
Aguascaliente Railroadmen of the Mexican League on Saturday at
Edison Field and then host Cal State Fullerton on Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
